{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Tdo2bGSEK9mMYz217qh4jb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` was missing the `configure` permission on the `/app` vhost. The RabbitMQ Management API's `PUT /queues/{vhost}/{queue}` endpoint requires `configure` permission to declare a queue. The user had `write` and `read` but the `configure` field was blank.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Verified end state:**\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are Running\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running` with 0 restarts\n- `/app` vhost contains `app-queue` of type `classic` (durable) with messages accumulating (29+ and growing)\n- `app-user` now has full `configure/write/read` permissions on `/app`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":261,"cache_read_input_tokens":33713,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":261},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d3888e9-639c-4804-9e22-073c0bf79043","uuid":"61e88d60-1a99-4d69-be10-e26d24f46fe1","request_id":"req_011CcdFCzWJJprjBsELNcL9q"}
